tspan.tspan: First, a copy of the head sgement is created and the
position of the copy is updated to be the next position
the head would have moved to.
The copy of the head sgement that was created is
inserted at the front of the chain as the new head
By creating a copy of the head and inserting it at the front of the chain, then removing the tail, we create an illusion that the
entire snake is moving without having to iterate every segement and manually reposition them.
The tails segement is removed from the end of the
chain to give the illusion of the snake moving forward.
